, 2021
</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9E0A5D6716E060B39DF947FE760830" blockId="21.[151,1437,1725,2040]" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">
Prior to this paper, many specimens of the more abundant prasinoid species (Ap2, Ap3) had been identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2171DE6716E060B39DF91BFEAC09AC" baseAuthorityName="Brauer" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[151,323,1761,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Apertochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis id="B955D64F6716E060B39DF91BFEAC09AC" box="[151,323,1761,1787]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">A. abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on the black costal crossveins and rows of abdominal black dots, which were considered crucial for distinguishing it from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2171DE6716E060B118F8FFFD660848" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1839" box="[530,649,1797,1823]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Chrysopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prasina">
<emphasis id="B955D64F6716E060B118F8FFFD660848" box="[530,649,1797,1823]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">A. prasina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB077AC6716E060B192F8FFFCC00877" author="Brauer, F." box="[664,815,1797,1824]" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" pagination="703 - 708" refId="ref18110" refString="Brauer, F. (1856) Ru ¨ ckblick auf die im Jahre 1850 beschriebenen o ¨ sterreichischen Arten der Gattung Chrysopa Leach nebst Beschreibung der Ch. tricolor n. sp.. Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 6, 703 - 708." type="journal article" year="1856">Brauer, 1856</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB077AC6716E060B036F8FFFC300848" author="Holzel, H." box="[828,991,1797,1823]" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" pagination="65 - 82" refId="ref18775" refString="Holzel, H. (1973 b) Zur Revision von Typen europa ¨ ischer Chrysopa Arten. Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 80, 65 - 82. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 75938" type="journal article" year="1973">Hölzel, 1973b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB077AC6716E060B0E6F8FFFBC80877" author="Holzel, H." box="[1004,1063,1797,1824]" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" pagination="3" refId="ref18854" refString="Holzel, H. (1995) [Abstract] Was ist unter Chrysopa prasina Burmeister 1839 zu verstehen? - Treffen Deutschsprachiger Neuropterologen. Galathea, Berichte des Kreises Nurnberger Entomologen e. V., Supplement 2, 3." type="journal article" year="1995">1995</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB077AC6716E060B739F8FFFB800848" author="Holzel, H." box="[1075,1135,1797,1823]" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" pagination="409 - 420" refId="ref18896" refString="Holzel, H. (1998) Kommentare zu den von Friedrich Brauer in den Jahren 1850 und 1856 aus O ¨ sterreich beschriebenen Chrysopa species (Neuroptera: Chrysopidae). Stapfia, 55, 409 - 420." type="journal article" year="1998">1998</bibRefCitation>
). Now, especially with the description of Ap3, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2171DE6716E060B270F8D3FDCA0814" baseAuthorityName="Brauer" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[378,549,1833,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Apertochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis id="B955D64F6716E060B270F8D3FDCA0814" box="[378,549,1833,1859]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">A. abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has become a rather rare and particular species, apparently restricted to areas dominated by conifers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
